                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d717">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/581: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-30T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 30, 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 30—5:42 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My March 30, 11 a.m., in process of being dispatched. I have just been informed
                    by C. T. Wang that he has summarized his negotiations with Lampson by telegram
                    for C. C. Wu, who has been instructed to press negotiations in Washington.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
